{"files":{},"source":"https:\/\/excalidraw.com","version":2,"type":"excalidraw","appState":{"shouldCacheIgnoreZoom":false,"exportScale":2,"defaultSidebarDockedPreference":false,"openMenu":null,"showWelcomeScreen":true,"currentItemStrokeColor":"#1e1e1e","bindMode":"orbit","exportWithDarkMode":false,"lockedMultiSelections":{},"currentItemRoughness":1,"currentItemTextAlign":"left","exportBackground":true,"scrolledOutside":false,"selectedElementIds":{},"zenModeEnabled":false,"currentItemStartArrowhead":null,"zoom":{"value":0.92972699999999997},"theme":"light","activeTool":{"locked":false,"fromSelection":false,"lastActiveTool":null,"type":"selection","customType":null},"exportEmbedScene":false,"gridStep":5,"lastPointerDownWith":"mouse","selectedGroupIds":{},"currentItemBackgroundColor":"transparent","scrollY":-2041.1480558550445,"penDetected":false,"viewBackgroundColor":"#ffffff","name":"Untitled-2026-02-24-1904","currentItemFontFamily":8,"currentItemArrowType":"round","currentItemOpacity":100,"preferredSelectionTool":{"type":"selection","initialized":true},"scrollX":-233.60626477112538,"stats":{"open":false,"panels":3},"objectsSnapModeEnabled":false,"gridSize":20,"gridModeEnabled":false,"openSidebar":null,"currentItemRoundness":"round","currentItemStrokeStyle":"solid","editingGroupId":null,"previousSelectedElementIds":{},"currentChartType":"bar","currentItemStrokeWidth":2,"cursorButton":"up","currentItemEndArrowhead":"arrow","currentItemFillStyle":"solid","currentItemFontSize":16,"selectedLinearElement":null,"penMode":false},"elements":[{"seed":702877394,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"LRB7Vo9xS0yG9qGH6hpcW","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":36,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771940101310,"locked":false,"text":"Key Value Store","version":34,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"a0","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Key Value Store","height":45,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#e03131","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1155779534,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":577,"angle":0,"y":195,"width":297},{"seed":1454031762,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"yRW3F1BP4xxUK4EBCNF2G","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":16,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771940236635,"locked":false,"text":"Functional Requirements:\n\n- put(key,value)\n- get(key, value)\n\n— delete, update\n— ttl\n— versioning\n","version":269,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"a1","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Functional Requirements:\n\n- put(key,value)\n- get(key, value)\n\n— delete, update\n— ttl\n— versioning\n","height":180,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":318847054,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":387.7890625,"angle":0,"y":308.2265625,"width":211.20004272460938},{"seed":1758540558,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"0nPxjIY0NHsvXujCx2MRw","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":16,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771940290026,"locked":false,"text":"Non Functional Requirements:\n\n- Highly Available\n- Highly scalable\n- Eventual Consistency\n- Low latency","version":115,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"a2","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Non Functional Requirements:\n\n- Highly Available\n- Highly scalable\n- Eventual Consistency\n- Low latency","height":120,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1481166226,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":716,"angle":0,"y":309,"width":246.40005493164062},{"seed":545398414,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"EApTtzzgwC9Cr5ZFg-72d","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":16,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771941078751,"locked":false,"text":"Core components and techniques\n\n- Data partition ( to make system highly scalable we need to store data in multiple servers )\n- Data replication ( to make the system highly available we need to replicate data to multiple servers )\n- Data consistency\n- Inconsistency resolution\n- Handling failures","version":295,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"a3","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Core components and techniques\n\n- Data partition ( to make system highly scalable we need to store data in multiple servers )\n- Data replication ( to make the system highly available we need to replicate data to multiple servers )\n- Data consistency\n- Inconsistency resolution\n- Handling failures","height":140,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1177674766,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":384.51267392649032,"angle":0,"y":605.75738634634354,"width":915.19915771484375},{"seed":546900114,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"kSNfVyI0zBKz2JtaN670b","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":16,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771944353919,"locked":false,"text":"# Data Partition\n\n- problem with single server is that we are bounded to CPU, MEMORY, NETWORK, DISK limits.\n\n- To Avoid these we need to partition\/shard\/split the data to multiple servers\n\n- Now we are multiple servers in place we need to find out which key belongs to the which server\/partition\/shard?\n\n** Partitions strategies\n\n1. Range Based\n    \n    A-F -> server 1\n    G-N -> server 2\n    O-Z -> server 3\n\n    or numeric ranges\n\n    Pros\n    * Easy to understand \n    * Ordered data\n    * Good for range queries\n\n    Cons\n    * Rebalancing is painful\n    * Hotspot problem\n\n\n2. Hash Based\n\n    Server will be findout by some hash function\n\n    serverIndex = hash(key) % N (number of servers)\n\n    Pros\n    * Better distribution of data\n    * simpler\n\n    Cons\n    * Reblancing is really bad ( Massive data movements, might cause system instability )\n\n3. Consistent Hashing\n    \n    We create a hash space 0-2^128-1\n\n    Map both keys and nodes onto the same circular hashspace.\n\n    Key is owned by the first node clockwise from its position on the ring.\n\n    Pros\n    * Minimal data movement (1\/N)\n    \n    Cons\n    * Not uniform distribution  (all the nodes might get placed nearby and might increase load on some servers)\n\n\n4. Consistent Hashing with virtual Nodes\n\n    We place multiple virtual nodes on the hash ring for even\/smoother distribution.\n    \n    Faster recovery: When a node fails, its vnodes are spread across the ring, \n    so many nodes each take on a small slice rather than one neighbor absorbing all the load.","version":1382,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"a4","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"# Data Partition\n\n- problem with single server is that we are bounded to CPU, MEMORY, NETWORK, DISK limits.\n\n- To Avoid these we need to partition\/shard\/split the data to multiple servers\n\n- Now we are multiple servers in place we need to find out which key belongs to the which server\/partition\/shard?\n\n** Partitions strategies\n\n1. Range Based\n    \n    A-F -> server 1\n    G-N -> server 2\n    O-Z -> server 3\n\n    or numeric ranges\n\n    Pros\n    * Easy to understand \n    * Ordered data\n    * Good for range queries\n\n    Cons\n    * Rebalancing is painful\n    * Hotspot problem\n\n\n2. Hash Based\n\n    Server will be findout by some hash function\n\n    serverIndex = hash(key) % N (number of servers)\n\n    Pros\n    * Better distribution of data\n    * simpler\n\n    Cons\n    * Reblancing is really bad ( Massive data movements, might cause system instability )\n\n3. Consistent Hashing\n    \n    We create a hash space 0-2^128-1\n\n    Map both keys and nodes onto the same circular hashspace.\n\n    Key is owned by the first node clockwise from its position on the ring.\n\n    Pros\n    * Minimal data movement (1\/N)\n    \n    Cons\n    * Not uniform distribution  (all the nodes might get placed nearby and might increase load on some servers)\n\n\n4. Consistent Hashing with virtual Nodes\n\n    We place multiple virtual nodes on the hash ring for even\/smoother distribution.\n    \n    Faster recovery: When a node fails, its vnodes are spread across the ring, \n    so many nodes each take on a small slice rather than one neighbor absorbing all the load.","height":1240,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":818021454,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":379.73846990565562,"angle":0,"y":876.69346452870855,"width":994.3990478515625},{"seed":688040398,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"zKjuk9KU6OGE191P-bBBt","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":16,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771944564765,"locked":false,"text":"# Data Replication\n\n- With data replication we can get high availability and durability\n- Perfromance also increases as data is available in the closest server.\n\n- Here we look for N distinct servers to replicate the data.\n- As we have virtual nodes on hash ring we look for N different servers so that we get better reliability\n\n\n- Data replication comes with few challenges like replication strategies, data consistency etc.","version":443,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"a5","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"# Data Replication\n\n- With data replication we can get high availability and durability\n- Perfromance also increases as data is available in the closest server.\n\n- Here we look for N distinct servers to replicate the data.\n- As we have virtual nodes on hash ring we look for N different servers so that we get better reliability\n\n\n- Data replication comes with few challenges like replication strategies, data consistency etc.","height":200,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1621376462,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":384.65376820701482,"angle":0,"y":2292.5636677372918,"width":923.9991455078125}]}